    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "the wand thing makes sense i think, but is there a specific term for that weird connection? i remember reading something about it being called something \"spooky\" or something like that. can u explain why people say that?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Yes, the term you're thinking of is \"spooky action at a distance,\" which was coined by Albert Einstein, who was famously puzzled by the concept of quantum entanglement. He used the term \"spooky\" because he couldn't wrap his head around how two particles could be connected in such a way that the state of one instantly affects the state of the other, even if they're light-years apart. Einstein believed that there must be some hidden variable or a \"local\" explanation for this phenomenon, but quantum entanglement seems to defy that, showing that the universe is far more mysterious and interconnected than we could have ever imagined. So, when people say it's \"spooky,\" they're acknowledging the strange and seemingly impossible nature of this quantum connection.",
