    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "makes sense. so if even einstein thought it was spooky, is it basically just something we can't explain with current physics, or is there actually something \"hidden\" going on behind the scenes that we just haven't caught yet?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Quantum entanglement is indeed one of those phenomena that still baffles scientists, even with our current understanding of physics. While Einstein and others have proposed various hidden variable theories to explain it, no such theory has been proven to be correct. The current view, based on experiments and the principles of quantum mechanics, is that entanglement is a fundamental aspect of the quantum world, and it doesn't necessarily require a hidden variable to explain it. It's like discovering a new kind of magic that doesn't fit into our existing understanding of the universe, and we're still trying to figure out how it works. So, while the \"spooky\" nature of quantum entanglement might suggest there's something hidden going on, it's more likely that our current theories just aren't enough to fully explain it. The quest to understand this mysterious connection continues, and who knows, maybe one day we'll uncover a new, mind-blowing theory that sheds light on the true nature of quantum entanglement.",
      "source": "target",
